{
  "text": "The protocol for culturing human umbilical vein endothelial cell spheroids [CITATION_1] was adapted for use with rat skeletal muscle microvascular endothelial cells. Endothelial cells were plated at a density of 1000 cells/well in 96-well round bottom plates in 50 ml 0.8% medium viscosity carboxymethylcellulose (Sigma-Aldrich #C4888) in complete DMEM. Spheroids were formed by incubating 96-well plates at 37uC, 7% CO 2 for 4 to 7 days. Spheroids were lifted by brief trypsinization and then resuspended in neutralized acid-solubilized 2.5 mg/ml rat tail type 1 collagen (BD Biosciences #354236). Collagen-embedded spheroids were treated with corticosterone for 24 and 48 hours. Digital images of the spheroids were captured and sprout lengths quantified using Metamorph image analysis software.",
